        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "Leukoencephalopathy-dystonia-motor neuropathy syndrome is a peroxisomal neurodegenerative disorder characterized by spasmodic torticollis dystonic head tremor intention tremor nystagmus hyposmia and hypergonadotrophic hypogonadism with azoospermia. Slight cerebellar signs (left-sided intention tremor balance and gait impairment) are also noted. Magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) shows bilateral hyperintense signals in the thalamus butterfly-like lesions in the pons and lesions in the occipital region whereas nerve conduction studies of the lower extremities shows a predominantly motor and slight sensory neuropathy."
        },
